{
  "spec_version": "1.0",
  "id": "paperclip",
  "display_name": "Paperclip",
  "version": "1.4.0",
  "author": "agent-core team",
  "description": "Paperclip — open-source agent orchestration platform. Read and manage issues, agents, goals, approvals, and costs across one or more companies. One binding covers all companies your board key can access.",
  "setup": {
    "instructions": "Connect Agent Core to a self-hosted Paperclip install.\n\nAgent Core acts as a board operator, not a Paperclip agent, so you need a Board API key (not an agent key). One binding covers all companies your key can access — pass company_id per action call.\n\n## Getting the API key\n\n**Option A — Paperclip CLI (recommended):**\n1. Authenticate as a board user:\n   ```\n   paperclipai auth login\n   ```\n   This opens a browser approval flow and stores your board credential locally.\n2. Mint a named board API key (printed once — copy it now):\n   ```\n   paperclipai token board create --name agent-core\n   ```\n   The returned token starts with `pcp_board_...`.\n\n**Option B — via curl (requires an existing board session):**\n```\ncurl -X POST {base_url}/api/board-api-keys \\\n  -H 'Authorization: Bearer <your-board-session-token>' \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\"name\": \"agent-core\"}'\n```\nCopy the key from the response — shown once only.\n\n## Finding your company IDs\nCall get_me after creating the binding — the response lists all companyIds your key can access. Or open the Paperclip web UI; the URL contains /companies/{companyId}.\n\n## Binding config\n- base_url: Paperclip server root, e.g. http://paperclip-host:3100 (no trailing slash, no /api suffix)\n- api_key: Board API key from above (pcp_board_...)\n\nNote: Agent Core blocks private/loopback base_url values (localhost, 127.0.0.1, 172.x) unless that host is on the internal-host allowlist. For a same-host Paperclip, allowlist its address or reach it over a proxied/public hostname.",
    "documentation_url": "https://paperclip.ing/docs"
  },
  "credential_schema": {
    "fields": [
      {
        "name": "api_key",
        "type": "string",
        "secret": true,
        "required": true,
        "description": "Board API key from Paperclip (pcp_board_...). Create one with: paperclipai auth login, then paperclipai token board create --name agent-core."
      }
    ]
  },
  "requires": {
    "config": ["base_url"]
  },
  "actions": [
    {
      "name": "get_me",
      "description": "Verify the connection and return board operator identity — user ID, all accessible company IDs, and key info. Call this first to discover your company IDs.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {}
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "list_issues",
      "description": "List issues in a company, sorted by priority. Filter by status, assignee, or project.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["company_id"],
        "properties": {
          "company_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Paperclip company ID. Call get_me to list all company IDs your key can access."
          },
          "status": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Comma-separated status filter, e.g. 'todo,in_progress'. Valid values: backlog, todo, in_progress, in_review, blocked, done, cancelled."
          },
          "assignee_agent_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Filter by assigned agent UUID."
          },
          "project_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Filter by project ID."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "get_issue",
      "description": "Get a single issue by ID, including its plan document, parent chain, project, and goal.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["issue_id"],
        "properties": {
          "issue_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The issue ID (e.g. PROJ-42 or a UUID)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "create_issue",
      "description": "Create a new issue in a company.",
      "side_effect": "write",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["company_id", "title"],
        "properties": {
          "company_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Paperclip company ID."
          },
          "title": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Issue title."
          },
          "description": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Issue description (markdown)."
          },
          "status": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Initial status. Default: todo.",
            "enum": ["backlog", "todo", "in_progress", "blocked"]
          },
          "priority": {
            "type": "string",
            "enum": ["urgent", "high", "medium", "low"]
          },
          "assignee_agent_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Agent UUID or shortname to assign."
          },
          "parent_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Parent issue ID for sub-issues."
          },
          "project_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Project ID to associate the issue with."
          },
          "goal_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Goal ID to associate the issue with."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "update_issue",
      "description": "Update an existing issue. Optionally include a comment in the same call. Provide run_id when calling during an agent heartbeat.",
      "side_effect": "write",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["issue_id"],
        "properties": {
          "issue_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The issue ID to update."
          },
          "title": {"type": "string"},
          "description": {"type": "string", "description": "Issue description (markdown)."},
          "status": {
            "type": "string",
            "enum": ["backlog", "todo", "in_progress", "in_review", "blocked", "done", "cancelled"]
          },
          "priority": {
            "type": "string",
            "enum": ["urgent", "high", "medium", "low"]
          },
          "assignee_agent_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Reassign to this agent UUID or shortname."
          },
          "comment": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Optional comment to add alongside the update."
          },
          "run_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Current run ID (X-Paperclip-Run-Id header). Required for audit trail during heartbeats."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "checkout_issue",
      "description": "Atomically claim an issue and transition it to in_progress. Returns 409 if another agent owns it — do not retry on 409. Idempotent if you already own it.",
      "side_effect": "write",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["issue_id", "agent_id"],
        "properties": {
          "issue_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The issue ID to check out."
          },
          "agent_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The agent UUID claiming the issue."
          },
          "expected_statuses": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {"type": "string"},
            "description": "Statuses you expect the issue to be in. Defaults to ['todo','backlog','blocked','in_review']. Include 'in_progress' to re-claim after a crashed run.",
            "default": ["todo", "backlog", "blocked", "in_review"]
          },
          "run_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Current run ID (X-Paperclip-Run-Id header)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "release_issue",
      "description": "Release ownership of an issue so another agent can pick it up.",
      "side_effect": "write",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["issue_id"],
        "properties": {
          "issue_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The issue ID to release."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "add_comment",
      "description": "Post a comment on an issue. @-mentions (@AgentName) trigger heartbeats for the mentioned agent.",
      "side_effect": "write",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["issue_id", "body"],
        "properties": {
          "issue_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The issue ID to comment on."
          },
          "body": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Comment body (markdown). Use @AgentName to mention and wake an agent."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "list_comments",
      "description": "List all comments on an issue.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["issue_id"],
        "properties": {
          "issue_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The issue ID."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "list_agents",
      "description": "List all agents in a company.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["company_id"],
        "properties": {
          "company_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Paperclip company ID."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "list_goals",
      "description": "List all goals in a company.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["company_id"],
        "properties": {
          "company_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Paperclip company ID."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "list_approvals",
      "description": "List approval requests in a company. Filter by status (e.g. 'pending').",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["company_id"],
        "properties": {
          "company_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Paperclip company ID."
          },
          "status": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Filter by approval status, e.g. 'pending'."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "get_costs_summary",
      "description": "Get total spend, budget, and utilization for a company for the current month.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["company_id"],
        "properties": {
          "company_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Paperclip company ID."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "list_activity",
      "description": "Query the audit trail of all mutations in a company. Filter by agent, entity type, or entity ID.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["company_id"],
        "properties": {
          "company_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Paperclip company ID."
          },
          "agent_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Filter by actor agent ID."
          },
          "entity_type": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Filter by entity type: issue, agent, approval."
          },
          "entity_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Filter by specific entity ID."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "list_runs",
      "description": "List heartbeat runs for a company, newest first. Optionally filter by agent or cap the result count.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["company_id"],
        "properties": {
          "company_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Paperclip company ID."
          },
          "agent_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Filter to runs for a specific agent UUID."
          },
          "limit": {
            "type": "integer",
            "description": "Max runs to return (1–1000, default 200)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "list_live_runs",
      "description": "List currently queued or running heartbeat runs for a company. Use minCount to also include recent completed runs when the live count is low.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["company_id"],
        "properties": {
          "company_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Paperclip company ID."
          },
          "min_count": {
            "type": "integer",
            "description": "If live run count is below this, pad with recent completed runs (0–20)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "get_run",
      "description": "Get a single heartbeat run by ID.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["run_id"],
        "properties": {
          "run_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Heartbeat run UUID."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "cancel_run",
      "description": "Cancel an active heartbeat run. Board key required. Returns the cancelled run record.",
      "side_effect": "write",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["run_id"],
        "properties": {
          "run_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Heartbeat run UUID to cancel."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "get_run_events",
      "description": "List events emitted during a heartbeat run. Supports pagination via afterSeq.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["run_id"],
        "properties": {
          "run_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Heartbeat run UUID."
          },
          "after_seq": {
            "type": "integer",
            "description": "Return only events after this sequence number (for polling, default 0)."
          },
          "limit": {
            "type": "integer",
            "description": "Max events to return (default 200)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "get_run_log",
      "description": "Read raw stdout/stderr log bytes for a heartbeat run. Supports byte-range pagination.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["run_id"],
        "properties": {
          "run_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Heartbeat run UUID."
          },
          "offset": {
            "type": "integer",
            "description": "Byte offset to start reading from (default 0)."
          },
          "limit_bytes": {
            "type": "integer",
            "description": "Max bytes to return (default 256000)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "list_issue_runs",
      "description": "List currently live (queued or running) heartbeat runs associated with a specific issue.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["issue_id"],
        "properties": {
          "issue_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Issue ID or identifier (e.g. PROJ-42)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "get_issue_active_run",
      "description": "Get the currently active heartbeat run for an issue, if any. Returns null when the issue has no live run.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["issue_id"],
        "properties": {
          "issue_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Issue ID or identifier (e.g. PROJ-42)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "pause_agent",
      "description": "Pause an agent and cancel its active run. Board key required. The agent will not accept new heartbeats while paused.",
      "side_effect": "write",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["agent_id"],
        "properties": {
          "agent_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Agent UUID to pause."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "resume_agent",
      "description": "Resume a paused agent so it can accept heartbeats again. Board key required.",
      "side_effect": "write",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["agent_id"],
        "properties": {
          "agent_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Agent UUID to resume."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "terminate_agent",
      "description": "Terminate an agent and cancel its active run. Board key required. More forceful than pause — use when an agent is stuck.",
      "side_effect": "write",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["agent_id"],
        "properties": {
          "agent_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Agent UUID to terminate."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "wakeup_agent",
      "description": "Send a wakeup to trigger an agent heartbeat. Returns the new run, or 202 with a skip reason if the agent is already running or paused.",
      "side_effect": "write",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["agent_id"],
        "properties": {
          "agent_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Agent UUID to wake."
          },
          "reason": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Human-readable reason for the wakeup, shown in run history."
          },
          "payload": {
            "type": "object",
            "description": "Optional JSON payload passed to the agent's heartbeat context."
          },
          "force_fresh_session": {
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "Start a fresh session even if the agent has an existing one."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "list_projects",
      "description": "List all projects in a company.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["company_id"],
        "properties": {
          "company_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Paperclip company ID."}
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "get_project",
      "description": "Get a single project by ID, including its workspaces.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["project_id"],
        "properties": {
          "project_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Project ID or slug."}
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "create_project",
      "description": "Create a new project in a company.",
      "side_effect": "write",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["company_id", "name"],
        "properties": {
          "company_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Paperclip company ID."},
          "name": {"type": "string", "description": "Project name."},
          "description": {"type": "string", "description": "Optional project description."}
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "list_project_workspaces",
      "description": "List workspaces attached to a project.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["project_id"],
        "properties": {
          "project_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Project ID."}
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "list_skills",
      "description": "List all company skills (shared instruction bundles) for a company.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["company_id"],
        "properties": {
          "company_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Paperclip company ID."}
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "get_skill",
      "description": "Get details of a single company skill.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["company_id", "skill_id"],
        "properties": {
          "company_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Paperclip company ID."},
          "skill_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Skill ID or slug."}
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "get_skill_file",
      "description": "Read a file from a company skill's instruction bundle. Default file is SKILL.md.",
      "side_effect": "read",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["company_id", "skill_id"],
        "properties": {
          "company_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Paperclip company ID."},
          "skill_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Skill ID or slug."},
          "path": {"type": "string", "description": "Relative file path within the skill bundle (default: SKILL.md)."}
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "import_skills",
      "description": "Import one or more skills from a remote source (e.g. a GitHub repo slug like 'paperclipai/paperclip/paperclip'). Returns imported skill list and any warnings.",
      "side_effect": "write",
      "input_schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["company_id", "source"],
        "properties": {
          "company_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Paperclip company ID."},
          "source": {"type": "string", "description": "Skill source identifier, e.g. 'paperclipai/paperclip/paperclip'."}
